{"questionId":"3018983","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>There are only <strong>three</strong> integer sets of values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>, that form an AS-linear function.&nbsp;One of these is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>write down an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>;</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award marks as appropriate in parts (e) (ii) and (iii) for use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mi>b</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3018983","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ2.2ei","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"write down an expression for r2-r1 in terms of a and b;","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
